I'm using Eclipse 2.1.2, VSSPlugin 1.5.0, Windows XP, JDK 1.4.1 and observe the 
following behaviour:

When I compare a Java file with its more recent version in SourceSafe, 
sometimes the right pane of Java Source compare shows empty content, whereas 
the Java structure pane shows correctly the changes I have made.
This doesn't occur with non-Java files.

I think that with Eclipse 2.1.1, this has never happened.

There where no changes in that area between 2.1.1 and 2.1.2.
Is there any information in Eclipse's .log file?

It seems a problem related with the VSSplugin, because I have this in the
